为什么要进行正态性检验 (Normality Test)？

  • 正态分布/高斯分布是统计中最重要的分布，因为很多自然现象都服从正态分布，如血压、身高、测量误差、回归残差、学生成绩等；

  • 大多数参数检验 (e.g., correlation, regression, t-test, analysis of variance (ANOVA), Pearson’s correlation coefficient) 的一个可靠假设是数据近似服从正态分布。如果一组数据是非正态的，则通常需要采用非参数的检验方法 (e.g. Mann-Whitney test, Spearman’s correlation coefficient)，这将是更复杂的；

  • 正态分布具有很多优良的性质，中心极限定理 (CLT) 指出，在温和的条件下，从同一分布中独立得到的许多随机变量的均值近似正态分布，而与原始分布的形式无关；

图示检验法

# 生成两组数据
n <- 100
data.norm <- rnorm(n) # 正态分布
data.f <- rf(n, 10, 10) # F分布

直方图和密度估计

  • 直方图和密度图可以直观地判断数据分布是否呈钟形。
grap_test <- function(gen.data) {
  # 直方图和密度估计
  hist(gen.data, freq=FALSE)
  lines(density(gen.data), col="blue", lwd=2)
  # 添加正态密度
  curve(dnorm(x, mean=mean(gen.data), sd=sd(gen.data)), 
        from=min(gen.data), to=max(gen.data),
        col="red", lwd=2, add=TRUE)
  mtext(paste0("mu = 0; sigma = 1; ", "\n", 
               "mean = ", round(mean(gen.data),3), 
               "; sd = ", round(sd(gen.data),3)), side=3, cex=0.7)
}
par(mfrow=c(1, 2))
grap_test(data.norm) ;grap_test(data.f)

采用R package: ggplot2

library(plyr)
library(ggplot2)
df <- data.frame(x=c(data.norm, data.f),
                 type=factor(rep(c("norm", "F"), each=n)))
mu <- ddply(df, "type", summarise, grp.mean=mean(x))

ggplot(df, aes(x=x)) + 
  geom_histogram(aes(y=..density..), binwidth=0.2, colour="black", fill="white") +
  scale_x_continuous(limits=c(-5, 5)) +
  geom_density(alpha=.2, fill="#FF6666") +
  geom_vline(data=mu, aes(xintercept=grp.mean), color="blue",
             linetype="dashed") + # 添加均值线
  facet_grid(type ~ .) +
  theme_bw()

ggplot(df, aes(x=x, fill=type, color=type)) +
  geom_histogram(aes(y=..density..), binwidth=0.2, position="identity", alpha=0.5) +
  geom_density(alpha=0.6) +
  scale_x_continuous(limits=c(-5, 5)) +
  geom_vline(data=mu, aes(xintercept=grp.mean, color=type),
             linetype="dashed") + # 添加均值线
  scale_color_grey() + 
  scale_fill_grey() +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(legend.position="top") # 标签放置在顶部

Q-Q plot & P-P plot

Q-Q Plot

qq_test <- function(gen.data) {
  qqnorm(gen.data, pch=20, cex=1)
  qqline(gen.data, col="gray60", lwd=2)
}
par(mfrow=c(1, 2))
qq_test(data.norm) ;qq_test(data.f)

尝试自己用函数实现Q-Q plot

qq_func <- function(gen.data) {
  sample.quan <- qnorm((rank(gen.data) -0.5)/length(gen.data)) # -0.5是常用的修正方法
  plot(sample.quan, gen.data, pch=20, cex=1,
       xlab="Theoretical Quantiles", ylab="Sample Quantiles",
       main="Q-Q plot")
  # # 快速计算累积百分数
  # sample.quan <- qnorm(ppoints(length(gen.data)))
  # plot(sample.quan, sort(gen.data), pch=20, cex=1,
  #      xlab="Theoretical Quantiles", ylab="Sample Quantiles",
  #      main="Q-Q plot")
  
  abline(mean(gen.data), sd(gen.data), col="red", lwd=2)
  # 利用qqnorm函数
  qqnorm(gen.data, pch=20, cex=1)
  qqline(gen.data, col="red", lwd=2)
}
par(mfrow=c(2, 2))
qq_func(data.norm); qq_func(data.f)

同时Q-Q图还可以检验两组数据是否来自同一个分布

# plot(quantile(data.norm, seq(0, 1, by=0.001)), 
#      quantile(data.f, seq(0, 1, by=0.001)),
#      xlab="data.norm", ylab="data.f")
plot(quantile(data.norm, sort(rank(data.norm)/length(data.norm))), 
     quantile(data.f, sort(rank(data.f)/length(data.f))),
     xlab="data.norm", ylab="data.f")

P-P plot

  • 横轴为实际累积概率，纵轴为理论分布累积的概率，标准直线为 \(y=x\)
pp_test <- function(gen.data) {
  sample.quan <- (rank(gen.data)-0.5)/length(gen.data)
  plot(sample.quan, pnorm(mean=mean(gen.data), sd=sd(gen.data), gen.data), 
       xlab="Sample Cumulative Probability", ylab="Theoretical Cumulative Probability", 
       main="P-P plot")
  abline(0, 1, col="red", lwd=2)
}
par(mfrow=c(1, 2))
pp_test(data.norm); pp_test(data.f)

统计量检验法

  • 参考文章: Comparisons of various types of normality tests

  • \(H_{0}: f(x, \Theta) \in N\left(\mu, \sigma^{2}\right)\) vs \(H_{1}: f(x, \Theta) \notin N\left(\mu, \sigma^{2}\right)\)

Moments

  • 来自 tseries package 的函数 jarque.bera.test()

jarque.bera.test(data.f)

##  Jarque Bera Test

## X-squared = 53.865, df = 2, p-value = 2.011e-12
# ??JarqueBeraTest

## alternative hypothesis: data have a skewness

Skewness test

常见分布的偏度值：

  • Normal distribution has a skewness of 0

  • Half-normal distribution has a skewness of just below 1

  • Exponential distribution has a skewness of 2

  • Lognormal distribution can have a skewness of any positive value, depending on its parameters

n <- 10000
nl <- rnorm(n) # Normal distribution
skewness(nl)
## [1] 0.02135579
rln <- rlnorm(n) # Lognormal distribution
skewness(rln)
## [1] 5.141755
el <- rexp(n) # exponential distribution
skewness(el)
## [1] 2.046103
# ??Skew

Kurtosis test

  • 任何一元正态分布的峰度都是3
n <- 10000
nl <- rnorm(n) # Normal distribution
kurtosis(nl)
## [1] 3.00416
rln <- rlnorm(n) # Lognormal distribution
kurtosis(rln)
## [1] 54.26995
el <- rexp(n) # exponential distribution
kurtosis(el)
## [1] 8.907842
# ??Kurt
library(DescTools)
Kurt(nl, method=2) # 函数中已经-3，接近0为正态分布
## [1] 0.00476274

Empirical distribution test

Kolmogorov-Smirnov (KS) test

ks.test(data.norm, "pnorm", mean=mean(data.norm), 
        sd=sd(data.norm), alternative="two.sided")
## 
##  One-sample Kolmogorov-Smirnov test
## 
## data:  data.norm
## D = 0.06384, p-value = 0.8097
## alternative hypothesis: two-sided
ks.test(data.norm, "pnorm", mean=3, 
        sd=10, alternative="two.sided")
## 
##  One-sample Kolmogorov-Smirnov test
## 
## data:  data.norm
## D = 0.5258, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: two-sided
